title: H.S. girls volleyball wrap: Rutherford tops Pascack Hills
text:
H.S. girls volleyball wrap: Rutherford tops Pascack Hills October 25, 2015 Last updated: Sunday, October 25, 2015, 1:21 AM The Record Print 
OLD TAPPAN – Senior Jessica Rogers and Group 1 Rutherford have come on strong in October. 
Rogers had a team-high 13 kills and eight digs as the No. 10 Bulldogs defeated No. 7 Pascack Hills, 25-22, 25-21, in Saturday’s round of 16 at the 41st Bergen County girls volleyball tournament. 
Sophomore setter Anna DeCesare handed out 20 assists as Rutherford (17-4) stretched its record in this month to 10-1, with its only loss coming to unbeaten River Dell. 
BOGOTA 2, MAHWAH 1: Junior hitter Samantha Gioiosa had 22 kills as the No. 9 Bucs extended their winning streak to 13 by defeating the No. 8 Thunderbirds, 25-16, 17-25, 25-22. Senior setter Amanda Manzo had 34 assists and sophomore Lisbeth Suarez 18 digs for Bogota (19-2). 
TENAFLY 2, RAMAPO 0: Senior hitter Noy Chorin had 14 kills and 11 digs and senior setter Anna Stein 16 assists as the No. 6 Tigers (21-5) edged the No. 11 Green Raiders, 25-22, 27-25. 
RIVER DELL 2, HOLY ANGELS 1: The No. 3 Golden Hawks staved off the No. 14 Angels, 28-26, 24-26, 25-22, to improve to 19-0. Junior setter Meredith Arancio contributed 34 assists. 
IMMACULATE HEART 2, RIDGEWOOD 0: Senior hitter Casey King had 12 kills and nine digs and senior setter Caitlyn Floyd 19 assists as the two two-time defending champion and No. 2 Blue Eagles posted a 25-12, 25-21 win. 
NV/OLD TAPPAN 2, NORTHERN HIGHLANDS 0: Senior hitter Natalie Alechko had eight kills and senior setter Kelly Brogan 19 assists as the top-seeded Golden Knights improved to 16-0 with a 25-12, 26-24 victory.
